    <abstract>
      <t>This document describes three new SRv6 end point behaviors, named END.REPLACE, END.REPLACEB6 and END.DB6. These SIDs are used in distributed inter-domain solutions for connecting SRv6 domains. This behavior is normally executed on border routers between different domains. These SIDs can also be used to provide multiple intent based paths across these domains.</t>
